title: The Saw Doctors - 2009-03-13 - Nokia Theatre Times Square - New
description:
Yet another fine show from the Saw Docs. Features former Saw Docs bassist Pearse Doherty on four tunes (playing the whistle and singing), and Davy's son on "Hay Wrap". Also includes two songs recorded, but not yet released, "Friday Town" and "Someone Loves You".

The thump in the left channel during "That's What She Said Last Night" is due to the drunken woman behind me trying to get me to dance. You can probably also hear her tunelessly wailing along during "Tommy K".

The opening set by Bearfoot was also recorded, and will be posted soon.


The Saw Doctors
Nokia Theatre Times Square
New York, NY
March 13, 2009
